# .deploy-token.example  →  copy to ".deploy-token" and paste your GitHub PAT
#
# The nightly "publish" scheduled task pushes to GitHub unattended using a token
# stored in a sibling file named ".deploy-token" in this folder (gitignored).
#
# One-time setup (run on your Mac):
#   1. Create a fine-grained Personal Access Token:
#        https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#      - Resource owner:        shenhuang
#      - Repository access:     Only select repositories -> shenhuang/blue
#      - Permissions -> Repository -> Contents: Read and write
#      - Generate token, copy it (starts with github_pat_...).
#   2. Save it as a single line, no quotes, no trailing newline/space:
#        printf '%s' 'PASTE_TOKEN_HERE' > "/Users/huangshen/Desktop/Blue/.deploy-token"
#        chmod 600 "/Users/huangshen/Desktop/Blue/.deploy-token"
#
# .deploy-token is gitignored and is NEVER committed or pushed.
# Delete it any time to disable unattended publishing.
